title: BREAKING: Donald Trump's 'Muslim ban' will NOT extend to any other nations 'at this time'
text:
BREAKING: Donald Trump's 'Muslim ban' will NOT extend to any other nations 'at this time' BREAKING: Donald Trump's 'Muslim ban' will NOT extend to any other nations 'at this time' DONALD Trump’s government has revealed no other countries will be facing the travel order imposed on seven Muslim-majority nations. PUBLISHED: 23:02, Fri, Feb 3, 2017 | UPDATED: 23:10, Fri, Feb 3, 2017 GETTY Donald Trump will not extend his executive order to any other nation 
The US Homeland Security Department released a statement claiming no other country will be joining the list “at this time”. 
Tens of thousands of visas have been revoked under Trump's travel ban, the State Department says. Related articles Donald Trump’s travel ban: THIS country may be next on the list 
The ban includes restricting access to the US for refugees and some visa holders from Iraq, Iran, Libya, Somalia, Sudan, Syria and Yemen. 
The order has been met with stiff opposition as hundreds of thousands took to the streets across the world to protest against Trump’s directive. 
More to follow.
